@NODE AF "System Requirements"

  OS 2.0+


  Although I have no means to test it on a 2.0+ system, I see no reason
  why it shouldn't work.



  Compiled with SAS/C 6.57 and tested on an A1200/030 with 6Mb RAM.

@ENDNODE


@NODE AG Installation

  Just copy it to your C: directory.

@ENDNODE


@NODE AH Usage

  Type 'C:Flash' at your DOS prompt:

    INDEX/A,OUTDIR/A,DELETE/S


    INDEX:  Full path and name of your index file.

    OUTDIR: This is where the output files will be written.

    DELETE: Optional, if specified, the index file will be deleted.


  Example:

    C:Flash Comms:Download/Index Comms:Aminet DELETE

    - Opens your index file Comms:Download/Index.
    - Writes the output to the directory: Comms:Aminet.
    - Deletes the file Comms:Download/Index after splitting has finished.


  IMPORTANT !!!

  Make sure that the output directory is empty before using Flash. Because
  of internal operation, existing files will be appended!

  I myself use a DOS script called 'Split' like this:


  C:Delete Comms:Aminet/#? QUIET
  C:Date
  C:Flash Comms:Download/Index Comms:Aminet DELETE
  C:Date

@ENDNODE


